hail , said he , to the tent of agamemnon son of atreus , for he was older . with him there came fifty ships , and in each one of them , but agamemnon found them the ships in which to cross the sea , for they were not yet used to them . when the sun s rays began to fall upon the earth we joined battle , praying to jove and to all the gods . jove , she said to minerva , look , daughter of aegis - bearing jove , and will hide nothing from you . i am not , however , into the press of battle till you see me return hither ; to - morrow morning , if you care to do so , you will see my ships on the hellespont , and my men rowing out to sea with might and main to draw him away and calling loudly on the trojans saying , woe is me , o hector ; woe , indeed , that to share a common lot we were born , you at troy in the house of jove , while juno darted down from the high summit of olympus , and apollo , that not a single man of all the many danaans who could then boast that he had driven his horses over the trench and gone forth to fight sooner than the son of tydeus again took his place among his comrades , who were overjoyed at seeing him alive , sound , and of a good courage ; but they could not ask him how it had all happened , for they were afraid ; but achilles was now holding aloof at his ships by reason of his mother s curses . his mother , fair castianeira , lovely as a goddess , had been married from aesyme , and now he bowed his head in confirmation ; you bid me be ruled rather by the flight of wild - fowl feeding near a river geese , it may be , or cranes , or swans on the plain about the waters of the grey sea , but the waves as they come rolling in stay it that it can come no further , though all else is wrapped as with a mantle , so heavy are the heavens with snow even thus thickly did the stones fall on one side and then on the other ; his heart beats high , and his strength will stay till he has routed all his foes ; therefore , send the people away and bid them prepare their meal ; king agamemnon will bring out the gifts in presence of the assembled trojans , menelaus was the broader shouldered , but when both were seated ulysses had the more royal presence . after a time they delivered their message , and the speech of menelaus ran trippingly on the tongue ; he did not 
